TITLE: Elon Musk's Twitter Takeover Seen Swelling the Company's Debt
SUMMARY: The social-media platform’s annual interest burden will climb to more than $1 billion from $51 million last year, analysts estimate, adding pressure to grow sales.

TITLE: Medtronic to Spin Off Patient-Monitoring, Respiratory Interventions Businesses
SUMMARY: The medical-technology and services company said the businesses were slightly below its overall performance in terms of gross margin and revenue growth.

TITLE: Europe's Economy Contracts as Tough Winter Looms
SUMMARY: Business activity in Europe fell for a fourth straight month in October, according to new surveys, as the continent enters a crucial phase of its economic conflict with Russia.

TITLE: Timeshare Comes to the Office
SUMMARY: Some companies are saving money on space by alternating days in a workplace with other firms.

TITLE: Schlumberger Rebrands as SLB, Dropping Family Name
SUMMARY: The oil-field services giant says new name marks commitment to cleaner energy.

TITLE: Tesla Cuts Prices in China as Costs Fall, Competition Heats Up
SUMMARY: Tesla has lowered prices for vehicles sold in China, days after Chief Executive Elon Musk said most materials costs are falling and amid growing competition from local rivals.

TITLE: Philips to Cut 4,000 Jobs as Big Recall, Supply Snags Hit Earnings
SUMMARY: The Dutch healthcare conglomerate said that the job cuts, which amount to about 5% of its 80,000 workforce, would save Philips almost $300 million a year.

TITLE: Rising Shipping Costs Prompt Businesses to Get Creative
SUMMARY: Entrepreneurs and executives say that to cope they are buying their own delivery vehicles, pleading with customers for patience and changing the products they sell.

TITLE: Higher Interest Rates Can Take a Long Time to Bring Down Inflation
SUMMARY: Lags between rate increases and real-world impacts raise the twin risks of tightening too much and too little.

TITLE: China's Economy Grew 3.9% in the Third Quarter
SUMMARY: China’s economy grew more strongly than expected in the third quarter as the country bounced back modestly from crippling Covid lockdowns in the spring, though challenges remain.

TITLE: Biden Pitches Plan to Refill Oil Reserves, but Producers Are Skeptical
SUMMARY: The administration is offering to buy oil at fixed future prices, but U.S. oil companies are wary of boosting output.

TITLE: Economy Week Ahead: U.S. GDP and Wages; Monetary Policy Abroad
SUMMARY: Data and interest-rate decisions will provide a picture of the global economy’s health in the face of high inflation and disruptions related to the Ukraine war.

TITLE: 'Black Adam' Revives Weekend Box Office
SUMMARY: The Warner Bros. movie out of its DC Films studio stars Dwayne “The Rock” Johnson and took in $67 million.

TITLE: How U.S. Supply Chain Sway Throttles China's Chip Development
SUMMARY: New U.S. export restrictions are targeting areas including semiconductor design and essential manufacturing equipment.

SUMMARY: Cash-strapped European consumers are flocking to discount stores, company executives say, as the prices of many goods, from food and clothing to electricity and gasoline, keep rising.

TITLE: Early Earnings Reports Worry Investors Battered by Stock Selloff
SUMMARY: So far in the third-quarter earnings-reporting season, fewer companies than usual are beating Wall Street’s expectations.

TITLE: Facebook Says It Is Prepared to Block News Content in Canada
SUMMARY: The social-media company says it wasn’t invited to testify in parliamentary review of news-media legislation.

TITLE: Meta-Backed Meesho Is Beating Amazon, Walmart in Race for Indian Shoppers
SUMMARY: The upstart e-commerce service is posing a challenge to the U.S. retailing titans, which have plowed billions of dollars into the world’s biggest untapped digital market.
